description: The northwestern city of Ardebil experienced the first snowfall on Wednesday, causing some schools and educational centers across the city to be shut down.
title: Ardebil hosts first autumn snowfall

description: TEHRAN –Supported by the Vice-Presidency of Science and Technology, the second Isfahan Artificial Intelligence (IAI) Event kicked off today in Isfahan and will conclude on Friday.
title: Isfahan hosting AI Event 2024

description: TEHRAN – By the end of the current Iranian year (March 20, 2025), two million undocumented foreign nationals who are residing and working in the country will be located and sent back to their home countries, the Iranian Police Chief, Brigadier General, Ahmad Reza Radan, has said.
title: Some 2 million illegal refugees to be expelled: official

description: TEHRAN –The Red Crescent Society of Kyrgyzstan (RCSK) has said it welcomes the Iranian Red Crescent Society (IRCS) to expand services in Kyrgyzstan.
title: RCSK invites IRCS to boost services in Kyrgyzstan

description: TEHRAN –Climate change, global warming, seasonal transitions, and intense drought in the world have not only destroyed the environment but have also made people’s lives more difficult.
title: Importance of social resilience, responsibility against climate change

description: TEHRAN- Production of alumina powder in Iran stood at 96,685 tons during the first five months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-August 21), according to the data released by Iranian Mines and Mining Industries Development and Renovation Organization (IMIDRO).
title: Over 96,000 tons of alumina powder produced in 5 months

description: TEHRAN – According to a report by the Islamic republic of Iran Shipping Lines (IRISL), Six cranes in Iran’s southeastern Chabahar Port have been equipped with container unloading and loading tools, so the container operation capacity of the port has reached 100,000 TEUs.
title: Chabahar Port’s container capacity to reach 100,000 TEUs

description: TEHRAN – In a joint meeting between the customs and agriculture committees of the Iran Chamber of Commerce, Industries, Mines and Agriculture (ICCIMA), the director general of the Transit Office of the Islamic Republic of Iran Customs Administration (IRICA) called on the private sector to invest in the country’s customs to modernize their equipment.
title: IRICA calls on private sector to invest in customs

description: TEHRAN – Based on the latest data released by the Islamic Republic of Iran Customs Administration (IRICA), some 6,720,659 cellphone handsets, valued at $1.497 billion, were imported into the country in the first seven months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20–October 21).
title: Cellphones imports drop 9% in 7 months yr/yr

description: TEHRAN - The head of the Islamic Republic of Iran Customs Administration (IRICA) said 25,448 passenger cars were imported into the country in the first seven months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-October 21).
title: Over 25,000 passenger cars imported in 7 months

description: TEHRAN - The International Monetary Fund (IMF) has raised its economic growth forecast for Iran in 2024 amid signs the country is becoming increasingly immune to the economic impacts of U.S. sanctions.
title: IMF revises up its 2024 economic growth forecast for Iran

description: TEHRAN - Iran's national futsal team are facing a potential coaching change after a disappointing performance at the 2024 FIFA Futsal World Cup in Uzbekistan.
title: Shamsaei’s uncertain future in Iran futsal

description: TEHRAN – Esteghlal winger Mehrdad Mohammadi suffered a broken tibia and is set for surgery.
title: Mehrdad Mohammadi sidelined for three months

description: TEHRAN – Mohammad Naghousi of Iran won a gold medal in the 2024 U23 World Championships in Greco-Roman Tuesday night.
title: Greco-Roman wrestler Naghousi wins gold in U23 World Championships
